file.content:
components:
  schemas:
    tmp0:
      properties:
        dispositions: {type: string}
        modules: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp1:
      properties:
        type: {type: string}
        value: {type: string}
      type: object
  securitySchemes: {}
info:
  contact: {email: frikky@shuffler.io, name: '@frikkylikeme', url: 'https://twitter.com/frikkylikeme'}
  description: Automated generation of Cisco Threat Response
  title: Cisco Threat Response
  version: 1.0.0
  x-logo: data:image/png;base64,
openapi: 3.0.2
paths:
  tmp0:
    post:
      description: Get contextual information for the given observable.
      parameters:
      - description: The type of the observable to enrich (returned by Inspect Observables
          task).
        example: sha256
        in: query
        name: Type
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The value of the observable.
        example: f42dd791495a93802851cfc98975b0ced502d66f0cd11c2d1d3d0b145be91e95
        in: query
        name: Value
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp0'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Cisco Threat Response Enrich Observable
  tmp1:
    post:
      description: Get value and type from observable
      parameters:
      - description: A text string that you want to pull observables out of.
        example: test string with an ip 1.1.1.1 and a hash f42dd791495a93802851cfc98975b0ced502d66f0cd11c2d1d3d0b145be91e95
        in: query
        name: Investigation String
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp1'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Cisco Threat Response Inspect Observables
tags:
- {name: Investigation}
